  "body": "The current implementation accepts this code as valid:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncontract test {\r\n    function() {\r\n      (2 2 2);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis becomes really confusing if you accidentally use a C-like cast syntax (I wrote a parser, I should know better ðŸ™„ ):\r\n\r\n```\r\ncontract A {\r\n    function foo() {}\r\n}\r\n\r\ncontract B {\r\n    address addr;\r\n    \r\n    function() {\r\n        ((A) addr).foo();\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nsolc output:\r\n\r\n```\r\nbrowser/dowhile.sol:9:9: TypeError: Member \"foo\" not found or not visible after argument-dependent lookup in tuple(type(contract A),address)\r\n        ((A) addr).foo();\r\n        ^------------^\r\n```",
